Saudi Arabia’s Zakat and Tax Revenues Rise 11%, SPA Reports

-- B y   M o u r a d   H a r o u t u n i a n
-- 
2011-03-01T13:14:53Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-01/saudi-arabia-s-zakat-and-tax-revenues-rise-11-spa-reports.html
  Saudi Arabia ’s revenue from zakat
and taxes grew a combined 11 percent last year, the  Saudi Press
Agency  reported, citing the  Department of Zakat and Income Tax .  The amount raised from zakat, or Islamic social tax, rose
to 8.8 billion riyals ($2.4 billion) while taxes imposed on
foreign companies totalled 6.9 billion riyals, SPA said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mourad Haroutunian in Riyadh at 
 mharoutunian@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
